AGENTS.md:208:**Symptom:** Microsoft sign-in appeared to succeed (popup opened and closed) but the app showed "Microsoft sign-in failed." `POST /api/core/auth/azure` returned `401`. Cloud Run logged: `The request was not authorized to invoke this service. The access token could not be verified.`
AGENTS.md:210:**What broke and why:** Microsoft SSO itself was fine — Azure AD authenticated the user correctly. The failure was in the next step: the BFF proxying the user's Azure token to the backend. The BFF attaches a Google Cloud OIDC token to every backend request so Cloud Run accepts it (see §1). That Google OIDC token had the wrong `audience` claim because `CORE_BACKEND_URL` was set to the custom domain (`https://api.core.*.designflow.app`). Cloud Run validates OIDC token audiences against the service's `.run.app` URL only — custom domains are not accepted, even when they correctly route traffic to the service.
